<eesti>Seaduse reguleerimisala </eesti>
<inglise>Scope of application of Act </inglise>
<eesti>(1) K&auml;esolevas seaduses s&auml;testatakse riigisisese ja rahvusvahelise autoveo korraldamise alused. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) This Act provides the bases for the organisation of internal and international road transport. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) K&auml;esolev seadus ei reguleeri kaitsej&otilde;udude autoveo korraldust. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) This Act does not regulate the organisation of road transport by the Defence Forces. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 2. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 2. </inglise>
<eesti>M&otilde;isted </eesti>
<inglise>Definitions </inglise>
<eesti>K&auml;esolevas seaduses on kasutatud m&otilde;isteid j&auml;rgmises t&auml;henduses: </eesti>
<inglise>In this Act, the following definitions are used: </inglise>
<eesti>1) autovedu - s&otilde;itjate v&otilde;i veose kohaletoimetamine selleks etten&auml;htud ja kehtestatud korras registreeritud s&otilde;idukiga. </eesti>
<inglise>1) "road transport" means the carriage of passengers or goods by a vehicle which is designated therefor and which is registered pursuant to the established procedure. </inglise>
<eesti>Autovedu h&otilde;lmab ka s&otilde;itjate v&otilde;i veoseta s&otilde;iduki liikumist; </eesti>
<inglise>Road transport also includes the movement of a vehicle which is not carrying passengers or goods; </inglise>
<eesti>2) tasuline autovedu - s&otilde;itjate v&otilde;i veose kohaletoimetamine, mille eest vedaja saab tasu mis tahes vormis; </eesti>
<inglise>2) "road transport for hire or reward" means the carriage of passengers or goods for which the carrier receives reward in any form; </inglise>
<eesti>3) oma kulul korraldatav autovedu - s&otilde;itjate v&otilde;i veose kohaletoimetamine, mille eest vedaja tasu ei saa; </eesti>
<inglise>3) "road transport on own account" means the carriage of passengers or goods for which the carrier does not receive reward; </inglise>
<eesti>4) riigisisene autovedu - s&otilde;itjate v&otilde;i veose kohaletoimetamine Eesti piires; </eesti>
<inglise>4) "internal road transport" means the carriage of passengers or goods within Estonia; </inglise>
<eesti>5) rahvusvaheline autovedu - s&otilde;itjate v&otilde;i veose kohaletoimetamine riigipiiri &uuml;letades; </eesti>
<inglise>5) "international road transport" means the carriage of passengers or goods involving crossing the national border; </inglise>
<eesti>6) vedaja - autoveo tegevusluba omav &auml;riseadustikus (RT I 1995, 26-28, 355; 1998, 91-93, 1500; 1999, 10, 155; 23, 355; 24, 360; 57, 596; 102, 907; 2000, 29, 172; 49, 303; 55, 365; 57, 373; 2001, 34, 185; 56, 332 ja 336; 89, 532; 93, 565; 2002, 3, 6) nimetatud ja &auml;riregistrisse kantud ettev&otilde;tja v&otilde;i seaduse alusel teise registrisse kantud isik, oma kulul korraldatava autoveo puhul ka kohalik omavalitsus&uuml;ksus. </eesti>
<inglise>6) "carrier" means an undertaking who holds a licence for road transport, whose legal form is specified in the Commercial Code (RT I 1995, 26-28, 355; 1998, 91-93, 1500; 1999, 10, 155; 23, 355; 24, 360; 57, 596; 102, 907; 2000, 29, 172; 49, 303; 55, 365; 57, 373; 2001, 34, 185; 56, 332 and 336; 89, 532; 93, 565; 2002, 3, 6) and who is entered in the commercial register, or a legal person entered in another register pursuant to law and in the case of road transport on own account, also a local government; </inglise>
<eesti>(21.03.2002 seadus j&otilde;ust.18.04.2002 - RT I 2002, 32, 190) </eesti>
<inglise>(21.03.2002 entered into force 18.04.2002 - RT I 2002, 32, 190) </inglise>
