<eesti>&Uuml;lds&auml;tted </eesti>
<inglise>General provisions </inglise>
<eesti>(1) K&auml;esoleva peat&uuml;ki s&auml;tteid kohaldatakse veose tasulise veo korral, mida korraldatakse vedaja omandis oleva v&otilde;i rendile v&otilde;etud auto v&otilde;i autorongiga, mille registrimass &uuml;letab 3500 kilogrammi. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The provisions of this Chapter apply in the event of the carriage of goods for hire or reward using an automobile or road train which is owned or leased by a carrier and which has a maximum registered weight of more than 3500 kilograms. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) S&otilde;itjate tasulist autovedu reguleerib &uuml;histranspordiseadus (RT I 2000, 10, 58; 2001, 18, 85). </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The fee-charging carriage of passengers is regulated by the Public Transport Act (RT I 2000, 10, 58; 2001, 18, 85). </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 4. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 4. </inglise>
<eesti>Tasulise autoveo tegevusluba ja s&otilde;idukikaart </eesti>
<inglise>Activity licence and licence card for road transport for hire or reward </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Tasulise autoveo korraldamiseks peavad vedajal olema tegevusluba ja iga kasutatava mootors&otilde;iduki kohta s&otilde;idukikaart. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) In order to organise road transport for hire or reward, a carrier shall hold an activity licence and shall hold a licence card concerning each motor vehicle to be used. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Tasulise autoveo tegevusluba on dokument, mis t&otilde;endab selle omaniku &otilde;igust korraldada autovedu tasu eest. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) An activity licence for road transport for hire or reward is a document which certifies the right of the holder to organise road transport for hire or reward. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Tasulise autoveo s&otilde;idukikaart on k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 2 nimetatud tegevusloa alusel antav dokument, mis t&otilde;endab tegevusloa omaniku &otilde;igust kasutada s&otilde;idukikaardile kantud s&otilde;idukit tegevusloaga lubatud autoveol. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) A licence card for road transport for hire or reward is a document issued on the basis of the activity licence specified in subsection (2) of this section which certifies the right of the holder to use the vehicle entered on the licence card for road transport permitted by the activity licence. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Tasulise autoveo tegevusluba ja s&otilde;idukikaart antakse riigisisese v&otilde;i rahvusvahelise autoveo korraldamiseks. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) Activity licences and licence cards for road transport for hire or reward are issued for the organisation of internal or international road transport. </inglise>
<eesti>Tasulise rahvusvahelise autoveo tegevusluba annab &otilde;iguse korraldada ka riigisisest tasulist autovedu. </eesti>
<inglise>An activity licence for international road transport for hire or reward also grants the right to organise internal road transport for hire or reward. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Tasulise autoveo tegevusloa ja s&otilde;idukikaardita v&otilde;ib korraldada vedusid, mis veo iseloomust ja pikkusest tingituna ei oma autoveoturul olulist t&auml;htsust. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) Transport operations which are of no major importance to the road transport market due to the nature of the operations or length of the journey may be organised without an activity licence and licence card for road transport for hire or reward. </inglise>
<eesti>Selliste vedude loetelu kehtestab teede- ja sideminister. </eesti>
<inglise>The list of such transport operations shall be established by the Minister of Transport and Communications. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 5. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 5. </inglise>
<eesti>Tasulise autoveo tegevusloa taotlejale ja selle omanikule esitatavad n&otilde;uded </eesti>
<inglise>Requirements for applicants for and holders of activity licences for road transport for hire or reward </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Tegevusloa taotleja ja selle omaniku majandusseisund peab vastama k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect;-s 6 s&auml;testatud n&otilde;uetele. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The economic standing of applicants for and holders of activity licences shall meet the requirements provided for in &sect; 6 of this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Tegevusloa omaniku registreeritud tegevusala peab olema autoveoteenuse osutamine v&otilde;i seda h&otilde;lmav muu veondustegevus. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The registered area of activity of the holder of an activity licence shall be the provision of road transport services or other transport operations which includes the provision of road transport services. </inglise>
<eesti>Tegevusloa omanik peab tegevusala registreerima enne esimese s&otilde;idukikaardi taotluse esitamist. </eesti>
<inglise>The holder of an activity licence shall register such area of activity prior to submitting an application for a first licence card. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Tegevusloa taotleja v&otilde;i selle omanik peab m&auml;&auml;rama vedude eest vastutava isiku, kes korraldab vedaja veoteenuste osutamist ja vastab k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect;-s 7 s&auml;testatud n&otilde;uetele. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The applicant for or holder of an activity licence shall appoint a person responsible for transport operations who shall organise the provision of transport services by the carrier and meet the requirements provided for in &sect; 7 of this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>Vedaja v&otilde;ib m&auml;&auml;rata mitu vedude eest vastutavat isikut. </eesti>
<inglise>A carrier may appoint several persons responsible for transport operations. </inglise>
<eesti>Vedude eest vastutav isik v&otilde;ib olla ka f&uuml;&uuml;silisest isikust vedaja ise. </eesti>
<inglise>A carrier who is a natural person may appoint himself or herself as the person responsible for transport operations. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Tegevusloa omanik v&otilde;ib ajutiselt, kuid mitte &uuml;le &uuml;he aasta, tegutseda vedude eest vastutava isikuta, kui selle p&otilde;hjus on nimetatud isiku pikaajaline t&ouml;&ouml;v&otilde;imetus v&otilde;i surm. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) A holder of an activity licence may temporarily, but not for longer than one year, operate without a person responsible for transport operations if this situation is caused by the long-term incapacity for work or the death of the person. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Tegevusloa taotleja v&otilde;i selle omanik peab vastama hea maine n&otilde;udele. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) An applicant for or holder of an activity licence shall meet the requirement relating to good repute. </inglise>
<eesti>K&auml;esoleva seaduse m&otilde;ttes peetakse isiku mainet heaks, kui teda ei ole seoses varasema majandustegevusega &uuml;le kahe korra halduskorras karistatud maksu-, tolli-, hinna- ja tarbijakaitse ning t&ouml;&ouml;- ja puhkeaja n&otilde;uete rikkumise eest, k&auml;esolevas seaduses etten&auml;htud tegevusloa v&otilde;i s&otilde;idukikaardita veo korraldamise v&otilde;i riiklikku registrisse andmete esitamise korra rikkumise eest v&otilde;i kui karistuse &auml;rakandmisest on m&ouml;&ouml;dunud v&auml;hemalt kolm aastat. </eesti>
<inglise>For the purpose of this Act, a person is deemed to be of good repute if, in connection with the previous economic activities of the person, the person has not been punished by way of administrative procedure on more than two occasions for violation of tax, customs, price, consumer protection or working and rest time requirements, for organisation of transport operations without the activity licence or licence card prescribed by this Act, or for violation of the procedure for the submission of information to a register, or if at least three years have passed from the date on which the person finished serving a punishment. </inglise>
<eesti>(6) F&uuml;&uuml;silisest isikust tegevusloa taotleja v&otilde;i selle omaniku mainet peetakse heaks, kui ta lisaks k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 5 s&auml;testatule vastab ka k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 7 l&otilde;ikes 2 s&auml;testatud n&otilde;uetele. </eesti>
<inglise>(6) An applicant for or holder of an activity licence who is a natural person is deemed to be of good repute if, in addition to the requirements provided for in subsection (5) of this section, he or she also meets the requirements provided for in subsection 7 (2) of this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>(7) Tasulise rahvusvahelise autoveo tegevusloa taotlejal peab olema v&auml;hemalt kaheaastane riigisisese tasulise autoveo kogemus, mida ta t&otilde;endab tegevusloaga v&otilde;i muul viisil. </eesti>
<inglise>(7) An applicant for an activity licence for international road transport for hire or reward shall have at least two years' experience of internal road transport for hire or reward which the applicant shall certify with the activity licence or in any other manner. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 6. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 6. </inglise>
<eesti>Tasulise autoveo tegevusloa taotleja ja selle omaniku majandusseisund </eesti>
<inglise>Economic standing of applicants for and holders of activity licences for road transport for hire or reward </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Tegevusloa taotleja v&otilde;i selle omaniku majandusseisund on n&otilde;uetele vastav, kui ta k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 2 v&otilde;i 3 nimetatud andmetele tuginedes t&otilde;estab, et tal on ettev&otilde;tluse alustamiseks ja vedude n&otilde;uetekohaseks korraldamiseks vajalik rahaline seis. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The economic standing of an applicant for or holder of an activity licence is deemed to comply with the requirements if the applicant or holder can certify on the basis of the information specified in subsection (2) or (3) of this section that their financial position is adequate to commence business and organise transport operations according to the requirements. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Rahalise seisu hindamisel v&otilde;etakse aluseks raamatupidamise aastaaruanded. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Evaluation of the financial position shall be based on the annual accounts. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Raamatupidamise aastaaruannete puudumise korral v&otilde;etakse aluseks: </eesti>
<inglise>(3) In the absence of annual accounts, the following shall be taken into consideration: </inglise>
<eesti>1) raha pangakontol ja muud rahalised vahendid ning v&otilde;lad ja laenud; </eesti>
<inglise>1) cash at bank and other funds, and overdraft and loan facilities; </inglise>
<eesti>2) majandustegevuse stabiilsuse tagamiseks etten&auml;htud vara ja muu vara; </eesti>
<inglise>2) assets available to provide security for the undertaking, and other assets; </inglise>
<eesti>3) s&otilde;idukite, kinnistute, seadmete ja varustuse ostukulud v&otilde;i esimesed sissemaksed ning k&auml;ibekapital ja muud kulud. </eesti>
<inglise>3) purchase cost or initial payment for vehicles, registered immovables and plant and equipment, and working capital and other costs. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) &Uuml;hele mootors&otilde;idukile s&otilde;idukikaardi saamiseks peab tegevusloa omanik t&otilde;endama, et tal on omavahendeid v&auml;hemalt 140 000 krooni ulatuses; igale j&auml;rgmisele mootors&otilde;idukile s&otilde;idukikaardi saamiseks peab omavahendeid iga mootors&otilde;iduki kohta olema v&auml;hemalt 80 000 krooni. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) In order to be issued a licence card for one motor vehicle, the holder of an activity licence shall certify the existence of own funds of at least 140 000 kroons; in order to be issued subsequent licence cards, the existence of own funds of at least 80 000 kroons for each following motor vehicle shall be certified. </inglise>
<eesti>Omavahendite olemasolu t&otilde;endamiseks esitab tegevusloa omanik s&otilde;idukikaardi andjale j&auml;rgmised dokumendid: </eesti>
<inglise>The holder of an activity licence shall submit the following documents to the issuer of licence cards to certify the existence of own funds: </inglise>
<eesti>1) juriidilisest isikust vedaja esitab oma vara ja kohustuste auditeeritud seisu, mille fikseerimisest ei v&otilde;i olla m&ouml;&ouml;dunud rohkem kui kuus kuud. </eesti>
<inglise>1) a carrier who is a legal person shall submit the audited status of the carrier's assets and liabilities which shall be documented not later than six months prior to submission thereof. </inglise>
<eesti>Samal eesm&auml;rgil v&otilde;ib s&otilde;idukikaardi andja tunnustada v&otilde;i t&otilde;endusena n&otilde;uda panga v&otilde;i muu asjakohaste volitustega asutuse kinnitust v&otilde;i t&otilde;endit kas garantiikirjana v&otilde;i muul samav&auml;&auml;rsel viisil antud kinnituse v&otilde;i t&otilde;endina; </eesti>
<inglise>For the same purpose, the issuer of licence cards may accept or require as proof confirmation or certification in the form of a letter of guarantee, or issued in any other equivalent manner by a bank or other agency with appropriate authority; </inglise>
<eesti>2) f&uuml;&uuml;silisest isikust vedaja esitab panga v&otilde;i muu asjakohaste volitustega asutuse kinnituse v&otilde;i t&otilde;endi kas garantiikirjana v&otilde;i muul samav&auml;&auml;rsel viisil antud kinnituse v&otilde;i t&otilde;endina. </eesti>
<inglise>2) a carrier who is a natural person shall submit confirmation or certification in the form of a letter of guarantee or issued in any other equivalent manner by a bank or other agency with appropriate authority. </inglise>
<eesti>Samal eesm&auml;rgil v&otilde;ib vedaja esitada oma vara ja kohustuste auditeeritud seisu, mille fikseerimisest ei v&otilde;i olla m&ouml;&ouml;dunud rohkem kui kuus kuud. </eesti>
<inglise>For the same purpose, the carrier may submit the audited status of his or her assets and liabilities which shall be documented not later than six months prior to submission thereof. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 7. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 7. </inglise>
<eesti>Vedude eest vastutav isik </eesti>
<inglise>Person responsible for transport operations </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Vedude eest vastutav isik peab olema teov&otilde;imeline, vastama k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 2 s&auml;testatud hea maine n&otilde;udele ja olema ametialaselt p&auml;dev korraldama tasulist autovedu. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A person responsible for transport operations shall have active legal capacity, meet the requirement to be of good repute provided for in subsection (2) of this section and have the necessary professional competence to organise road transport for hire or reward. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Vedude eest vastutava isiku mainet peetakse heaks, kui: </eesti>
<inglise>(2) A person responsible for transport operations is deemed to be of good repute if: </inglise>
<eesti>1) teda ei ole kriminaalkorras karistatud v&otilde;i kui karistuse &auml;rakandmisest on m&ouml;&ouml;dunud v&auml;hemalt kolm aastat; </eesti>
<inglise>1) the person has not been punished pursuant to criminal procedure or more than three years have passed from the date on which the person finished serving a punishment; </inglise>
<eesti>2) tal ei ole seoses ametialase tegevusega &uuml;le kahe haldus&otilde;iguserikkumiste seadustiku (RT 1992, 29, 396; RT I 2001, 74, 453; 87, 524 ja 526; 97, 605; 102, 677; 2002, 18, 98; 21, 117; 29, 174 ja 175; 30, 176; 32, 189) &sect; 31 kohaselt kehtiva karistuse t&ouml;&ouml;j&otilde;u kasutamise, t&ouml;&ouml;tasustamise, veokorralduse, autojuhi t&ouml;&ouml;- ja puhkeaja reguleerimise, liiklusohutuse, s&otilde;idukite ohutuse v&otilde;i keskkonnakaitse valdkonnas. </eesti>
<inglise>2) in connection with the professional activities of the person, the person has no more than two punishments in force pursuant to &sect; 31 of the Code of Administrative Offences (RT 1992, 29, 396; RT I 2001, 74, 453; 87, 524 and 526; 97, 605; 102, 677; 2002, 18, 98; 21, 117; 29, 174 and 175; 30, 176; 32, 189) for offences committed in the field of the use of manpower, remuneration, organisation of transport operations, regulation of working and rest time of drivers, traffic or vehicle safety and environmental protection. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Vedude eest vastutavat isikut peetakse ametialaselt p&auml;devaks, kui ta on Teede- ja Sideministeeriumi tunnustatud &otilde;ppeasutuses l&auml;binud vedude eest vastutava isiku koolituskursuse ja sooritanud kursuse kirjaliku l&otilde;pueksami. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) A person responsible for transport operations is deemed to be professionally competent if he or she has undergone a training course for persons responsible for transport operations in an educational institution recognised by the Ministry of Transport and Communications and has passed the written final exam of the course. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Vedude eest vastutava isiku koolituskursust ei pea l&auml;bima isik, kes on v&auml;hemalt viis aastat olnud vedaja autoveo korraldaja ja on sooritanud k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 3 nimetatud koolituskursuse kirjaliku l&otilde;pueksami. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) A person who has worked as the organiser of transport operations with a carrier for at least five years and who has passed the written final exam of the training course specified in subsection (3) of this section is not required to undergo a training course for persons responsible for transport operations. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Vedude eest vastutava isiku koolituskursust ei ole vaja l&auml;bida ega l&otilde;pueksamit sooritada isikul, kellel on k&otilde;rgkoolidiplom erialal, mis t&otilde;endab piisavaid teadmisi koolituskursuse &otilde;ppekavas loetletud ainetes. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) A person who holds a diploma, issued by an institution of higher education, in an area of specialisation which certifies adequate expertise in the subjects listed in the curriculum of the training course for persons responsible for transport operations is not required to undergo the training course or pass the final exam of such training course. </inglise>
<eesti>(6) Teede- ja sideminister kinnitab vedude eest vastutava isiku kvalifikatsioonin&otilde;uded, koolituskursuse &otilde;ppekava, koolitustunnistuse vormi ning k&otilde;rgkoolide ja nendes ettevalmistatavate erialade loetelu, mille l&otilde;petajale antud k&otilde;rgkoolidiplom vastab k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 5 s&auml;testatule. </eesti>
<inglise>(6) The Minister of Transport and Communications shall approve the qualification requirements for persons responsible for transport operations, the curricula of training courses, the format of the certificates of training and a list of the institutions of higher education and areas of specialisation provided by such institutions which grant diplomas of higher education to their graduates in compliance with the provisions of subsection (5) of this section. </inglise>
