<eesti>&Uuml;lds&auml;tted </eesti>
<inglise>General provisions </inglise>
<eesti>(1) K&auml;esoleva peat&uuml;ki s&auml;tteid kohaldatakse oma kulul korraldatavale s&otilde;itjateveole autoga, milles koos juhikohaga on &uuml;le &uuml;heksa istekoha, ja oma kulul korraldatavale veoseveole auto v&otilde;i autorongiga, mille registrimass &uuml;letab 3500 kilogrammi. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The provisions of this Chapter apply to the carriage of passengers on own account using a motor vehicle having more than nine seats (the driver's seat included) and to the carriage of goods on own account using a motor vehicle or road train with a maximum registered weight of more than 3500 kilograms. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Oma kulul s&otilde;itjate- ja veoseveo korraldamiseks peavad olema t&auml;idetud j&auml;rgmised n&otilde;uded: </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The following requirements shall be met for the carriage of passengers or goods on own account: </inglise>
<eesti>1) autovedu on vedaja k&otilde;rvaltegevus; </eesti>
<inglise>1) road transport is a secondary activity of the carrier; </inglise>
<eesti>2) s&otilde;itjaid v&otilde;i veost vedav s&otilde;iduk on vedaja omandis v&otilde;i vedaja on v&otilde;tnud selle rendile; </eesti>
<inglise>2) the vehicle carrying passengers or goods is owned or leased by the carrier; </inglise>
<eesti>3) veol kasutatava s&otilde;iduki juht on vedaja t&ouml;&ouml;taja v&otilde;i vedaja ise; </eesti>
<inglise>3) the driver of the vehicle used in the transport operation is an employee of the carrier or the carrier himself or herself; </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Oma kulul veoseveo korraldamiseks peavad olema t&auml;idetud j&auml;rgmised lisan&otilde;uded: </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The following additional requirements shall be met for the carriage of goods on own account: </inglise>
<eesti>1) veos on vedaja omandis v&otilde;i vedaja on selle m&uuml;&uuml;nud, ostnud, rendile andnud v&otilde;i rendile v&otilde;tnud, tootnud, t&ouml;&ouml;delnud v&otilde;i parandanud; </eesti>
<inglise>1) the carrier owns the goods, has sold or bought the goods, is the commercial lessor or lessee of the goods or has produced, processed or improved the goods; </inglise>
<eesti>2) veost paigutatakse &uuml;mber ettev&otilde;ttes v&otilde;i v&auml;ljaspool ettev&otilde;tet omatarbeks. </eesti>
<inglise>2) the goods are relocated within or outside the enterprise for own consumption. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 9. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 9. </inglise>
<eesti>Oma kulul korraldatava autoveo tegevusluba ja s&otilde;idukikaart </eesti>
<inglise>Activity licence and licence card for road transport on own account </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Oma kulul korraldatavaks riigisiseseks autoveoks ei pea vedajal olema tegevusluba ega s&otilde;idukikaarti. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A carrier is not required to hold an activity licence or licence card for internal road transport on own account. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Oma kulul korraldatavaks rahvusvaheliseks autoveoks peavad vedajal olema tegevusluba ja iga kasutatava mootors&otilde;iduki kohta s&otilde;idukikaart. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) In order to organise international road transport on own account, a carrier shall hold an activity licence and shall hold a licence card concerning each motor vehicle to be used. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Oma kulul korraldatava rahvusvahelise autoveo tegevusluba on dokument, mis t&otilde;endab tegevusloa omaniku &otilde;igust korraldada rahvusvahelist autovedu oma kulul. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) An activity licence for international road transport on own account is a document which certifies the right of the holder to organise international road transport on own account. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Oma kulul korraldatava rahvusvahelise autoveo s&otilde;idukikaart on k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 3 nimetatud tegevusloa alusel antav dokument, mis t&otilde;endab tegevusloa omaniku &otilde;igust kasutada s&otilde;idukikaardile kantud s&otilde;idukit tegevusloaga lubatud autoveol. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) A licence card for international road transport on own account is a document issued on the basis of the activity licence specified in subsection (3) of this section which certifies the right of the holder to use the vehicle entered on the licence card for road transport permitted by the activity licence. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Rahvusvahelist autovedu v&otilde;ib oma kulul korraldada ka s&otilde;idukiga, mille kasutajale on antud s&otilde;idukikaart tasulise rahvusvahelise autoveo tegevusloa alusel. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) International road transport on own account may also be organised with a vehicle the user of which has been issued a vehicle card on the basis of an activity licence for international road transport for hire or reward. </inglise>
<eesti>(6) Oma kulul korraldatava rahvusvahelise autoveo tegevusloaga ei v&otilde;i korraldada tasulist vedu ega vedu, mis ei vasta k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 8 l&otilde;igetes 2 ja 3 s&auml;testatud n&otilde;uetele. </eesti>
<inglise>(6) An activity licence for international road transport on own account does not grant the holder of the licence the right to organise fee-charging carriage or transport operations which do not comply with the requirements provided for in subsections 8 (2) and (3) of this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 10. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 10. </inglise>
<eesti>Oma kulul korraldatava rahvusvahelise autoveo tegevusloa taotlejale ja selle omanikule esitatavad n&otilde;uded </eesti>
<inglise>Requirements for applicants for and holders of activity licences for international road transport on own account </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Oma kulul korraldatava rahvusvahelise autoveo tegevusloa taotleja peab taotlemisavalduses kinnitama, et ta korraldab vedu ainult oma kulul, ja nimetama tegevusala, millega veod on seotud. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) An applicant for an activity licence for international road transport on own account shall confirm in the application for the activity licence that the transport operations are organised solely on the applicant's own account and also specify the area of activity in connection with which the transport operations are organised. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Tegevusloa taotleja peab t&otilde;endama ja selle omanik tagama, et: </eesti>
<inglise>(2) An applicant for an activity licence shall certify and a holder of an activity licence shall guarantee that: </inglise>
<eesti>1) autovedu moodustab ainult osa ettev&otilde;tja &auml;ritegevusest, mille tulu ei &uuml;leta 50 protsenti kogu tulust, ning et veokulud kaetakse &auml;ritegevuse arvel; </eesti>
<inglise>1) road transport comprises only a part of the commercial activities of the undertaking, that revenue created thereby does not exceed 50 per cent of total revenue, and that the cost of transport is covered out of the commercial activities; </inglise>
<eesti>2) autovedu ei ole tema kui ettev&otilde;tja p&otilde;hitegevus, vaid &uuml;ksnes toetab seda. </eesti>
<inglise>2) road transport is not the principal activity of the undertaking but merely supports the principal activity. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Tegevusloa andja v&otilde;ib enne selle andmist n&otilde;uda tegevusloa taotlejalt nende dokumentide esitamist, mis t&otilde;endavad k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 2 nimetatud n&otilde;uetele vastavust. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The issuer of an activity licence may, prior to the issue thereof, require the applicant for the activity licence to submit documents in proof of compliance with the requirements specified in subsection (2) of this section. </inglise>
<eesti>4. peat&uuml;kk </eesti>
<inglise>Chapter 4 </inglise>
<eesti>Kombineeritud vedu </eesti>
<inglise>Combined Transport </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 11. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 11. </inglise>
<eesti>&Uuml;lds&auml;tted </eesti>
<inglise>General provisions </inglise>
<eesti>(1) K&auml;esolevas seaduses m&otilde;istetakse kombineeritud veona veose rahvusvahelist kohaletoimetamist autoga, vedukiga v&otilde;i vedukita poolhaagisega, auto vahetatava kerega v&otilde;i v&auml;hemalt 6,096 m (20 jala) pikkuse konteineriga, kui vedaja kasutab veo alg- v&otilde;i l&otilde;ppetapil maanteed ning &uuml;lej&auml;&auml;nud etappidel raudtee- v&otilde;i mereveoteenust sama saatedokumendi alusel. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) For the purposes of this Act, combined transport means the international transport of goods where the lorry, semi-trailer with or without tractor unit, swap body or container of 6.096 meters (20 feet) or more uses the road on the initial or final leg of the journey and, on the other leg, rail or maritime services on the basis of the same accompanying documents. </inglise>
<eesti>Raudtee- ja mereveoetapi algpunkti ja l&otilde;pp-punkti vaheline kaugus otsejoones m&otilde;&otilde;detuna peab olema &uuml;le 100 kilomeetri. </eesti>
<inglise>The distance between the initial and end-point of the section of the journey using rail or maritime services shall exceed 100 kilometres as the crow flies. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Kombineeritud veo algetapp on teel&otilde;ik veose pealelaadimise kohast kuni &uuml;mberlaadimiseks sobiva l&auml;hima raudteejaama v&otilde;i meresadamani ning l&otilde;ppetapp on teel&otilde;ik veose &uuml;mberlaadimiseks sobivast l&auml;himast raudteejaamast v&otilde;i meresadamast mahalaadimiskohani. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The initial leg of a combined transport operation is the section of the journey between the point where the goods are loaded and the nearest suitable rail loading station or seaport, and the final leg of a combined transport operation is the section of the journey between the nearest suitable rail unloading station or seaport and the point where the goods are unloaded. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Mereveo korral ei tohi kombineeritud veo alg- v&otilde;i l&otilde;ppetapi teel&otilde;igu pikkus peale- v&otilde;i mahalaadimise meresadamast otsejoones m&otilde;&otilde;detuna &uuml;letada 150 kilomeetrit. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) In the case of a maritime transport operation, the length of the section of the journey between the seaports of loading and unloading on the initial or final leg of a combined transport operation shall not exceed 150 kilometres as the crow flies. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 12. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 12. </inglise>
<eesti>Kombineeritud veo korraldamine </eesti>
<inglise>Organisation of combined transport </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Kui kombineeritud veo puhul korraldab veose saatja veo algetapil vedu k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 8 l&otilde;igete 2 ja 3 kohaselt oma kulul, ei ole nimetatud s&auml;tetega vastuolus veose saaja &otilde;igus toimetada veos veo l&otilde;ppetapil sihtkohta oma kulul. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Where, as a part of a combined transport operation, the dispatching undertaking carries out the initial leg for its own account within the meaning of subsections 8 (2) and (3) of this Act, the undertaking which is to receive the goods transported may, notwithstanding the definition given in this Act, carry out for its own account the final leg to transport the goods to their destination. </inglise>
<eesti>Veose saaja peab kasutama autot, mis on tema omandis v&otilde;i mille ta on v&otilde;tnud rendile ning mida juhib tema t&ouml;&ouml;taja v&otilde;i veose saaja ise. </eesti>
<inglise>The recipient of the goods shall use a vehicle owned or hired by the recipient and driven by an employee of the recipient or by the recipient himself or herself. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Rahvusvahelise kokkuleppe alusel v&otilde;ib kombineeritud autovedu korraldava vedaja vabastada k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect;-s 21 etten&auml;htud veoloa n&otilde;udest. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) On the basis of an international agreement, carriers organising combined road transport may be released from the obligation to hold the transport permit prescribed by &sect; 21 of this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Kombineeritud veol kasutatavas saatedokumendis peavad olema m&auml;rgitud raudteeveoga seotud peale- ja mahalaadimise raudteejaamad v&otilde;i mereveoga seotud peale- ja mahalaadimise sadamad. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The accompanying document for a combined transport operation shall set out the loading and unloading stations related to the rail leg of the transport operation and the loading and unloading seaports related to the maritime leg of the transport operation. </inglise>
<eesti>P&auml;rast veo l&otilde;ppemist teeb raudteejaama v&otilde;i sadama esindaja saatedokumenti sellekohase kande. </eesti>
<inglise>After the conclusion of a combined transport operation, a representative of each station or port shall make an entry to this effect in the accompanying document. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Kombineeritud veol kasutatavate s&otilde;idukite maksusoodustused s&auml;testatakse maksuseadustes. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) Tax incentives for vehicles used in combined transport shall be provided by Acts regulating tax issues. </inglise>
